reviewText: Seascape Capers is another dvd full of great episodes of SpongeBob Squarepants. Some of the funnier episodes are The Smoking Peanut, Krab Borg, Krusty Love, and Grandma's Kisses. I think what helps to make this such a great dvd is a minimum of Sandy. There were only two weak points in the dvd. One was no Plankton centered episode and the other is that they went rather light on the special features. There's only a storyboard sequence for Grandma's Kisses.

reviewText: SpongeBob: The Seascape CapersI don't know what it is about SpongeBob, but it is easily one of the cutest and funniest cartoons ever. It reminds me of the original Looney Tunes w/Bugs and Tweety(I don't know why, it just does).We own ALL of the SpongeBob DVDs(This year was a very SpongeBob Christmas) and my kids love this one the most. Maybe it's because there is 2 never before seen episodes on it?
